# Tailwind CSS & Component Markup Standards

**Next.js App Router | Tailwind v4 | TypeScript**

## Scope & Philosophy

These rules govern markup, styling, component architecture, and accessibility standards to ensure:

- **Consistency**: predictable patterns across the codebase
- **Maintainability**: clear structure and easy-to-understand code
- **Accessibility**: WCAG 2.1 AA compliance by default
- **Performance**: optimal bundle size and runtime efficiency

## Tailwind v4 Configuration

- **Token System**: All design tokens live in `src/app/globals.css` using `@theme inline` and CSS custom properties
- **Design Tokens First**: Always use semantic tokens (`bg-background`, `text-foreground`) over hard-coded values
- **Dark Mode**: Tokens automatically adapt via `prefers-color-scheme`; use `dark:*` modifiers only for exceptions
- **Utility-First Approach**: Write utilities inline; extract to separate CSS only when:
  - Complex selectors (3+ levels) make utilities unreadable
  - Third-party library overrides required (scope to library class, e.g., `.ag-theme-*`)
  - Animation keyframes or complex pseudo-elements needed

## Component Architecture

### File Structure & Location

```
src/components/
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ ui/                    # Shared primitives (Button, Input, Card, Badge, etc.)
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ <feature>/             # Feature-specific (table/, map/, search/, etc.)
‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ layout/                # Layout components (Header, Footer, Sidebar)

src/app/<route>/
‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ components/            # Route-local components (not reused elsewhere)
```

### Naming Conventions

- **Files**: PascalCase, one component per file (`SearchBar.tsx`, `UserProfile.tsx`)
- **Components**: Match filename; export as default
- **Subcomponents**: Export as named exports or compound pattern (`Card.Header`, `Card.Body`)
- **Props**: Use descriptive names; suffix types with `Props` (`ButtonProps`, `CardProps`)
- **Clear, Descriptive Names**: Use straightforward names that clearly indicate purpose
  - ‚úÖ Good: `TransactionCard`, `TimelineDot`, `ConnectorLine`, `PropertySearchBar`
  - ‚ùå Avoid: `Item`, `Thing`, `Component`, `Wrapper`, `Container` (too generic)
  - Names should be self-documenting and easy to reference in prompts/discussions

### Component Decomposition

- **Break Down Complex Components**: Split large components into focused subcomponents
- **Single Responsibility**: Each component should do one thing well
- **Composable**: Design components to work together through composition
- **Maximum Size**: If a component exceeds ~150 lines, consider splitting it
- **Example Structure**:
