### Component Structure Template

```tsx
"use client"; // Only if needed (hooks, events, browser APIs)

import { type ComponentPropsWithoutRef } from "react";

// Props interface with clear documentation
interface ButtonProps extends ComponentPropsWithoutRef<"button"> {
  /** Visual style variant */
  variant?: "primary" | "secondary" | "ghost" | "danger";
  /** Size preset */
  size?: "sm" | "md" | "lg";
  /** Show loading spinner */
  isLoading?: boolean;
}

export function Button({
  variant = "primary",
  size = "md",
  isLoading = false,
  className,
  children,
  disabled,
  ...props
}: ButtonProps) {
  // Build classes in logical groups
  const baseClasses =
    "inline-flex items-center justify-center gap-2 rounded-md font-medium transition-colors";
  const variantClasses = {
    primary: "bg-foreground text-background hover:opacity-90",
    secondary: "bg-foreground/10 text-foreground hover:bg-foreground/20",
    ghost: "bg-transparent text-foreground hover:bg-foreground/10",
    danger: "bg-red-600 text-white hover:bg-red-700",
  };
  const sizeClasses = {
    sm: "px-3 py-1.5 text-sm",
    md: "px-4 py-2 text-base",
    lg: "px-6 py-3 text-lg",
  };

  return (
    <button
      className={cn(
        baseClasses,
        variantClasses[variant],
        sizeClasses[size],
        "focus-visible:outline-none focus-visible:ring-2 focus-visible:ring-offset-2",
        "disabled:opacity-50 disabled:cursor-not-allowed",
        className
      )}
      disabled={disabled || isLoading}
      {...props}
    >
      {isLoading && <Spinner className="size-4" />}
      {children}
    </button>
  );
}
```

### Key Principles

- **Server-first**: Default to Server Components; add `'use client'` only when necessary
- **Composition**: Always accept `className` for style extension
- **Type Safety**: Extend native HTML element props (`ComponentPropsWithoutRef<'button'>`)
- **Accessibility**: Include ARIA attributes, keyboard navigation, focus management
- **Prop Forwarding**: Spread `...props` to support all native attributes

## Markup & Accessibility Standards

### Semantic HTML First

- **Use native elements**: `<button>`, `<nav>`, `<main>`, `<article>`, `<section>`, `<header>`, `<footer>`, `<h1>`-`<h6>`
- **ARIA as enhancement**: Only add ARIA when native semantics are insufficient
- **Interactive elements**: Use `<button>` for actions, `<a>` for navigation
- **Forms**: Always pair `<label>` with inputs using `htmlFor`/`id`

### Accessibility Checklist

‚úÖ **Keyboard Navigation**: All interactive elements focusable and operable via keyboard  
‚úÖ **Focus Indicators**: Visible focus states using `focus-visible:ring-2` or similar  
‚úÖ **Color Contrast**: Minimum 4.5:1 for text, 3:1 for UI components (WCAG AA)  
‚úÖ **Alt Text**: Descriptive `alt` for images; empty `alt=""` for decorative  
‚úÖ **Labels**: All form inputs have associated labels  
‚úÖ **Heading Hierarchy**: Logical order (h1 ‚Üí h2 ‚Üí h3), no skipping levels  
‚úÖ **Loading States**: Announce dynamic content with `aria-live` regions  
‚úÖ **Disabled States**: Use `disabled` attribute + visual indicators (`opacity-50`, `cursor-not-allowed`)

### Class Order Convention

Maintain this order for consistent, readable diffs:

1. **Layout**: `container`, `mx-auto`, `flex`, `grid`, `col-span-*`, `items-*`, `justify-*`, `content-*`, `place-*`
2. **Positioning**: `relative`, `absolute`, `fixed`, `sticky`, `inset-*`, `top-*`, `z-*`
3. **Display & Box Model**: `block`, `inline-block`, `hidden`, `w-*`, `h-*`, `min-*`, `max-*`, `overflow-*`, `aspect-*`
4. **Spacing**: `p-*`, `px-*`, `py-*`, `m-*`, `mx-*`, `my-*`, `gap-*`, `space-x-*`, `space-y-*`
5. **Typography**: `font-*`, `text-*` (size), `leading-*`, `tracking-*`, `uppercase`, `lowercase`, `capitalize`, `truncate`
6. **Visual Styling**: `bg-*`, `text-*` (color), `border`, `border-*`, `rounded-*`, `shadow-*`, `ring-*`, `outline-*`
7. **Effects**: `opacity-*`, `mix-blend-*`, `backdrop-*`, `filter`, `blur-*`, `brightness-*`
